Fashion designer #AlbertaFerretti held her resort show at Castel Sismondo, a fortress in Rimini, Italy, which was recently hit by severe floods. Despite the damage, Ferretti chose to keep the show on schedule as a way to demonstrate the region's resilience and determination to rebuild. The area is also the hometown of filmmaker Federico Fellini, who inspired Ferretti's collection with the region's soulful and sensual atmosphere. The show featured models walking on catwalks above pools of water, with scenes from Fellini's movies projected on the fortress walls and a soundtrack by Nino Rota adding to the dramatic atmosphere.
Ethereal Romance, Delicacy, & Strength 
Thank you @albertaferretti for having me and thank you most importantly for sharing your beautiful heart and soul with us!
